block content
	.articleContent
		div
			p Callouts can be used to highlight information within content, for example an important sentence, paragraph or paragraphs with multiple links.
			p There are 5 main callout styles:
			ul
				li warning
				li alert
				li useful
				li confirmation
				li example

			p Before using a callout, think about whether you really need it. Fewer callouts have more of an impact on a piece of content.
			p Too many callouts can confuse and distract clients from other important content on a page.
			p Callouts do not require headings by default but they can be used if they are relevant to the content.

			h3 Aria tags
			p The callouts are colour-coded to help users understand their importance. They also have #[code.code h2] or #[code.code h3] tags so that users know what the content’s about.
			p Some of the callouts use Aria tags to help visually impaired people. The Aria tags enable screenreaders to understand the information in the callouts.

			h2 Callout styles
			h3 Callout warning
			.example-box-plain
				.callout--warning
					p This callout style is used for important information that has serious and/or legal implications if the client doesn’t follow the advice. It uses the Aria tag #[code.code aria-label="Important"].
					//a.callout__link Callout link
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;div class="callout--warning"&gt;
					| 	&lt;h3&gt;Callout warning&lt;/h3&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;This callout style is used for important information that has serious and/or legal implications if the client doesn’t follow the advice. It uses the Aria tag &lt;code&gt;aria-label="Important"&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
					| &lt;/div&gt;

			h3 Callout alert
			.example-box-plain
				.callout--alert
					p This callout style should be used on important, non-mandatory advice for clients that doesn’t have any serious or legal implications. There might be other implications.
					p Use the Aria tag #[code.code aria-label="Help"].
					//a.callout__link Callout link
				//.callout--alert--icon
					h3 Callout alert with icon
					p The icon is optional and can be including by adding the #[code.code .callout--icon] class. For accessibility purposes use aria-label="Help"].
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;div class="callout--alert"&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;This callout style should be used on important, non-mandatory advice for clients that doesn’t have any serious or legal implications. There might be other implications.&lt;/p&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;Use the Aria tag &lt;code&gt;aria-label="Help"&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
					| &lt;/div&gt;

			h3 Callout unstyled
			.example-box-plain
				.callout
					p This callout style is for information that would be useful for clients to know. There wouldn’t be any legal implications for clients if they didn’t read the information.
					p This callout is useful for things like tips to help clients.
					p This callout needs an #[code.code h3] but doesn’t use an Aria tag.
					//a.callout__link Callout link
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;div class="callout"&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;This callout style is for information that would be useful for clients to know. There wouldn’t be any legal implications for clients if they didn’t read the information.&lt;/p&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;This callout is useful for things like tips to help clients.&lt;/p&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;This callout needs an &lt;code&gt;h3&lt;/code&gt; but doesn’t use an Aria tag.&lt;/p&gt;
					| &lt;/div&gt;


			h3 Callout confirmation
			.example-box-plain
				.callout--confirmation
					p This callout style is used to confirm an action.
				//.callout--confirmation--icon
					h3 Callout confirmation with icon
					p The icon is optional and can be including by adding the #[code.code .callout--icon] class.
					//a.callout__link Callout link
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;div class="callout--confirmation"&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;This callout style is used to confirm an action&lt;/p&gt;
					| &lt;/div&gt;


			h3 Callout example
			.example-box-plain
				.callout--example
					p This callout style is also known as a Blockquote and is used to highlight a quote or example within content.
					//a.callout__link Callout link
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;div class="callout--example"&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;Also referred to as Blockexample, this style is when a example needs to be displayed.&lt;/p&gt;
					| &lt;/div&gt;

			h3 Adviser content
			.example-box-plain
				.callout--adviser
					p This callout style is for content that only advisers should see. You should use it when you think advisers need more information to advise clients.
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;div class="callout--adviser"&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;This callout style is for content that only advisers should see. You should use it when you think advisers need more information to advise clients.&lt;/p&gt;
					| &lt;/div&gt;

			h3 Next steps
			p This callout is to show further reading or related links.
			p It is the only callout that requires a heading.
			.example-box-plain
				.callout--related
					h3 Next steps
					p Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat. Ut wisi enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exerci tation ullamcorper suscipit lobortis nisl ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Also #[a(href="#") including a link to other content].
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;div class="callout--related"&gt;
					| 	&lt;h3&gt;Next steps&lt;/h3&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat. Ut wisi enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exerci tation ullamcorper suscipit lobortis nisl ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Also &lt;a href="#"&gt; including a link to other content&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
					| &lt;/div&gt;

			h2 Combining callouts
			p The callouts can also be combined.
			p For example, you could have both a quote and an alert within an unstyled callout, or you could have a warning callout within a quote.
			p Here are some examples:

			.example-box-plain
				.callout
					p Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.
					.callout--example
						h3 This is a specific heading
						p Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.
					.callout--alert
						p Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;div class="callout"&gt;
					| 	&lt;h3&gt;Callout&lt;/h3&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.&lt;/p&gt;
					| 	&lt;div class="callout--example"&gt;
					| 		&lt;h3&gt;This is a example&lt;/h3&gt;
					| 		&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.&lt;/p&gt;
					| 	&lt;/div&gt;
					| 	&lt;div class="callout--alert"&gt;
					| 		&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.&lt;/p&gt;
					| 	&lt;/div&gt;
					| &lt;/div&gt;

			.example-box-plain
				.callout--example
					p Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.
					.callout--warning
						p Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;div class="callout--example"&gt;
					| 	&lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit.&lt;/p&gt;
					| 	&lt;div class="callout--warning"&gt;
